---
USING LINKED LISTS

Here are the functions of interest in this program:
   
            count(): count the elements in a linked list recursively
      find_vowels(): look for vowels and report results
           lookup(): lookup an element in the list recursively
   string_to_list(): create a linked list from a string recursively

---
It is easy to write iterative versions of the recursive functions
in this list, but because recursion works well in these kinds
of tasks, we are happy with the recursive versions.

---
The function fgets() that we used in main() picks up a line
typed at the keyboard, including a newline character.  All
of the characters in the line, including the newline
character, get counted.

